  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Ivabradine acts by inhibiting the ionic If current that modulates the pacemaker activity of
      sinoatrial node cells. The aim of present study is to evaluate the efficacy and safety of
      IvabRadine hemisulfate Sustained-release Tablets versus placebo in patients with moderate to
      severe chronic systolic heart failure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
